        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 27 at 6:53PM CDT by NWS Fort Worth TX</headline>
        <description>At 652 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Breckenridge, moving northeast at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph. This storm produced a wind gust
of 43 mph at the Breckenridge Airport.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Breckenridge, Possum Kingdom State Park, Possum Kingdom Lake, Ivan,
and Eliasville.
</description>
        <instruction>Frequent cloud to ground lightning is occurring with this storm.
Lightning can strike 10 miles away from a thunderstorm. Seek a safe
shelter inside a building or vehicle.</instruction>
